Why We Use Pages, Components, Services, and Types

Each module is divided into:

pages
components
services
types

Pages

Used for route-level screens.

Example:

UsersList.tsx
CreateCourse.tsx
EditLesson.tsx

Components

Used for reusable UI inside the module.

Example:

UsersTable.tsx
CourseForm.tsx
LessonResources.tsx

Services

Used for API calls.

Example:

usersApi.ts
coursesApi.ts
lessonsApi.ts

This keeps API logic separate from UI logic.

Types

Used for TypeScript types.

Example:

User
Course
Lesson
Purchase
Enrollment

This prevents using any and keeps the project clean.

---

Why Delete Pages Are Not Needed

We decided not to create separate delete pages.

Reason:

Deleting is usually a small confirmation action.

Instead, deletion will use:

ConfirmModal.tsx

Example:

Are you sure you want to delete this course?

Cancel
Delete

This is cleaner than creating:

DeleteCourse.tsx
DeleteUser.tsx
DeleteSubject.tsx

---

When To Use Separate Pages

Separate pages should be used for large forms or detailed views.

Examples:

CreateCourse.tsx
EditCourse.tsx
CourseDetails.tsx
CreateLesson.tsx
EditLesson.tsx
LessonDetails.tsx
UserDetails.tsx

Reason:

These pages contain many fields and complex logic.

---

When To Use Modal Forms

Modals can be used for simple actions.

Examples:

Confirm delete
Change status
Deactivate code
End session

But large forms should remain as pages.

---

Development Philosophy

The admin dashboard structure was designed to be:

Clean
Scalable
Professional
Easy to maintain
Easy to expand
Separated by responsibility
Compatible with large production projects

The structure avoids putting everything in one file.

It also avoids mixing API calls, UI components, and TypeScript types together.

